- Prototype a tool that offers users interesting questions to ask about bits and pieces of text.
- Use this tool to learn iteratively about what the user is interested in while reading an article.
- Use the tool to pose relevant articles for the reader to read, write summaries, and recommend similar articles.
- Add an outline feature to any blog generated.
- Notice what's missing, wrong, or bad, to investigate the problem further and develop solutions for it.
- Spend time becoming a Zen master who is naturally able to create beautiful art because of ease and love for the problem.
- Don't fear competition as it's a sign that there's a market and people want your product.
- Develop good habits of doing hard things that are not appealing.
- Avoid using recipes to have ideas and instead focus on looking for demand and investigating why some things are not there.